    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What are good alternatives if I enjoy Prosecco's style but want variety?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Cava from Spain offers similar fresh fruit character and food-friendliness at comparable prices, while Crémant de Loire provides more mineral-driven elegance with Loire Valley terroir expression. For domestic options, try sparkling wines from Virginia or Oregon made with similar tank methods, which offer Prosecco-like accessibility with regional character. Avoid comparing to Champagne directly, as these alternatives share Prosecco's approachable, fruit-forward philosophy rather than Champagne's complexity.</p>
