  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the biggest mistake people make when choosing Prosecco?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">The most common error is buying based solely on price, either choosing the cheapest option (which often lacks proper acidity and fruit character) or assuming expensive equals better quality. Many excellent Proseccos exist in the $15-25 range that outperform pricier options from lesser producers. Focus on reputable producers, proper DOCG or DOC designation, and recent vintage dates rather than flashy packaging or extreme pricing.</p>
